- [Tool]: [when to use it]

## Tips

- **Parallel sessions**: Use separate git worktrees (`git worktree add`) for
  running multiple Claude sessions on different tasks simultaneously.
- **Plan Mode default**: Start most sessions in Plan Mode (Shift+Tab x2).
  Only switch to implementation after the plan is approved.
- **MCP token cost**: Only enable MCP servers you actively use -- each adds
  to context overhead. Disable unused servers with `/mcp`.

